approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}.     * Requirements:     * - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

changeAPSManager(address).details: Function to change the APS Manager of the Vault.

params._vaultAPSManager: Address of the new APS Manager.

changeMasterCopy(address).details: Allows to upgrade the contract. This can only be done via a Safe transaction.

changeStrategyManager(address).details: Function to change the Strategy Manager of the Vault.

params._strategyManager: Address of the new Strategy Manager.

deactivateVaultStrategy(address).details: Function to deactivate a strategy in the vault.

params._strategyAddress: Address of the strategy to be deactivated.

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals used to get its user representation. For example, if `decimals` equals `2`, a balance of `505` tokens should be displayed to a user as `5,05` (`505 / 10 ** 2`).     * Tokens usually opt for a value of 18, imitating the relationship between Ether and Wei.     * NOTE: This information is only used for _display_ purposes: it in no way affects any of the arithmetic of the contract, including {IERC20-balanceOf} and {IERC20-transfer}.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically decreases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller.     * This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}.     * Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance.     * Requirements:     * - `spender` cannot be the zero address. - `spender` must have allowance for the caller of at least `subtractedValue`.

deposit(address,uint256).details: Function to Deposit assets into the Vault.

disableVaultStrategy(address,address[]).details: Function to disable a strategy along with the assets.

params._assetsToBeDisabled: List of assets to be disabled in Vault along with strategy.
params._strategyAddress: Address of the strategy to be disabled.

earn(address[],uint256[],bytes).details: Function to deposit vault assets to strategy

params._amount: list of asset amounts to deposit
params._assets: list of asset address to deposit

enableEmergencyExit().details: Function to enable Emergency Exit feature of the Vault.

getVaultActiveStrategy().details: Function to get the address of active strategy in the vault.

getVaultNAV().details: Function to return the NAV of the Vault.

getVaultNAVWithoutStrategyToken().details: Function to return the NAV of the Vault excluding Strategy Tokens.

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically increases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller.     * This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}.     * Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance.     * Requirements:     * - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

onERC1155Received(address,address,uint25.details: Function to perform operation on Receivel of ERC1155 token from Yieldster Strategy Minter.

registerVaultWithAPS().details: Function that is called once after vault creation to Register the Vault with APS.

setVaultActiveStrategy(address).details: Function to activate a strategy in the vault.

params._activeVaultStrategy: Address of the strategy to be activated.

setVaultAssets(address[],address[],addre.details: Function to manage the assets supported by the vaults.

params._disabledDepositAsset: List of assets to be disabled in Deposit assets.
params._disabledWithdrawalAsset: List of assets to be disabled in Withdrawal assets.
params._enabledDepositAsset: List of assets to be enabled in Deposit assets.
params._enabledWithdrawalAsset: List of assets to be enabled in Withdrawal assets.

setVaultSmartStrategy(address,uint256).details: Function to set smart strategies to vault.

setVaultStrategyAndProtocol(address,addr.details: Function to manage the Strategy and corresponding protocols supported by the vaults.

params._assetsToBeEnabled: List of assets to be enabled in Vault for the strategy.
params._disabledStrategyProtocols: List of protocols to be disabled in above strategy.
params._enabledStrategyProtocols: List of protocols to be enabled in above strategy.
params._vaultStrategy: Address of the strategy to be enabled.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: See {IERC165-supportsInterface}.     * Time complexity O(1), guaranteed to always use less than 30 000 gas.

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

toggleEmergencyBreak().details: Function to toggle Emergency Break feature of the Vault.

tokenValueInUSD().details: Function to return Value of the Vault Token.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}.     * Requirements:     * - `recipient` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `amount`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}.     * Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20};     * Requirements: - `sender` and `recipient` cannot be the zero address. - `sender` must have a balance of at least `amount`. - the caller must have allowance for `sender`'s tokens of at least `amount`.

withdraw(address,uint256).details: Function to Withdraw assets from the Vault.
